<subSubSection pageId="31" pageNumber="32" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="31.[151,1436,151,364]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,340,189,215]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Comments.</emphasis>
The species was fully redescribed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Crosskey, R. W." box="[813,1011,189,215]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" pagination="393 - 551" refId="ref28822" refString="Crosskey, R. W. (1962) A revision of the genus Pygophora Schiner (Diptera, Muscidae). Transactions of the Zoological Society of London, 29, 393 - 551." type="journal article" year="1962">Crosskey (1962)</bibRefCitation>
who mentioned that it is the most widespread species of 
<taxonomicName box="[415,545,226,251]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Pygophora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[415,545,226,251]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Pygophora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and who first recorded it from 
<collectingCountry box="[912,1012,226,252]" name="Vanuatu" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Vanuatu</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
